                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>When a bloodfog damages a creature with a misty tendril Strike, the creature must attempt a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:38] save. If the Strike was a critical hit, the outcome of the creature's save is one degree worse than the result of the saving throw. Any temporary Hit Points the bloodfog gains from blood siphon fade after 1 hour.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1}.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 1}, and the bloodfog gains 20 temporary Hit Points.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Drained]{Drained 2}. The bloodfog gains 40 temporary Hit Points and takes on an intense red hue until the end of its next turn. During this time, it gains a +2 status bonus to AC and saves and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Quickened]. It can use its extra action only to Strike.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Blood Siphon (Critical Failure)]</p>"
